<P><H1 align=center>DC150 – CCJ HISTORY</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>fields shown in 
red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT>            </P>
<P>If the applicant has had County Court Judgements against them, they will need 
to be recorded here. If the initial question ‘Have you ever had any County Court 
Judgements’ is answered YES by clicking the radio buttons, the ADD and EDIT 
buttons will become enabled.</P>
<P><H3>Add / Edit: </H3>Click on the ADD or EDIT button to move 
to screen <A HREF="HELP_DC151.asp">DC151, Add / Edit CCJ History</A>, where all details of the CCJ can be 
noted.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Main box: </H3>Any information taken will be summarised 
in the main box – name, value of judgement, plaintiff, monthly repayment, date 
cleared and any others responsible
<P></P>
<P><H3>Delete: </H3>To delete an existing CCJ entry, highlight 
the entry in the history box and click ELETE.
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>once details have been entered, click on ‘OK’ 
to lead to the next screen.
<P></P>
